headers.subject: [tosdr:2299] Yahoo! Services isn't responsible for your data

html:
You understand and agree that the Yahoo! Services is provided "AS-IS" and that Yahoo! assumes no responsibility for the timeliness, deletion, mis-delivery or failure to store any user communications or personalization settings.

 
This seems normal to me, and I'm not sure if we should make a point for this or not. If a user fails to store their emails on Yahoo! email, certainly that doesn't mean Yahoo! is liable for that.

http://info.yahoo.com/legal/us/yahoo/utos/terms/

--
